steps.text:
First, let's find the Jacobian of the transformation \( u = 2x - y \) and \( v = 2x + y \). The Jacobian matrix is given by:

\[
J = \begin{vmatrix}
\frac{\partial u}{\partial x} & \frac{\partial u}{\partial y} \\
\frac{\partial v}{\partial x} & \frac{\partial v}{\partial y}
\end{vmatrix}
= \begin{vmatrix}
2 & -1 \\
2 & 1
\end{vmatrix}
= 2 \cdot 1 - (-1) \cdot 2 = 4
\]

The absolute value of the determinant of the Jacobian is \( |4| = 4 \). So, the differential area element \( dydx \) transforms to \( \frac{1}{4} dvdu \).

